The paper focuses on automated GUI testing of a hybrid mobile application, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The use of Layout-based and Visual testing tools also suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). Finally, the specific context of mobile applications could also place the paper in the mobile computing (cs.MOBILE) sub-category.
